Description: Fragment of round handle from a Brindisi pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pale grey. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Latin inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Zeno. cf. Desy, Ph., Les timbres amphoriques de l'Apulie republicaine (Oxford 1989) 182. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 88, 5.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1298)
